From aec791a419070410122abc09eac2067c431b9858 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Huacai Chen <chenhuacai@loongson.cn>
Date: Thu, 17 Apr 2025 20:38:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 331/334] LOONGSON: LoongArch: Init acpi_gbl_use_global_lock to
 false

Init acpi_gbl_use_global_lock to false, in order to void error messages
during boot phase:

 ACPI Error: Could not enable GlobalLock event (20240827/evxfevnt-182)
 ACPI Error: No response from Global Lock hardware, disabling lock (20240827/evglock-59)

Signed-off-by: Huacai Chen <chenhuacai@loongson.cn>

https://github.com/chenhuacai/linux/commit/403a9b87c1c8aacda6d774b8b320e9923ac2d006
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 arch/loongarch/kernel/setup.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/loongarch/kernel/setup.c b/arch/loongarch/kernel/setup.c
index 66209f3cc253..67d26ef78501 100644
--- a/arch/loongarch/kernel/setup.c
+++ b/arch/loongarch/kernel/setup.c
@@ -357,6 +357,7 @@ void __init platform_init(void)
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_ACPI
 	acpi_table_upgrade();
+	acpi_gbl_use_global_lock = false;
 	acpi_gbl_use_default_register_widths = false;
 	acpi_boot_table_init();
 #endif
-- 
2.49.0

